<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-242-025 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 349 686</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 16 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for Macintosh: Sony Video Interface. (VBOX peripheralcontroller) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rosenbaum, Daniel J.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sony Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Sony VBOX (Peripheral controller) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionPeripheral Controllers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR MACINTOSH: Sony Video Interface 01/15/91 SAN FRANCISCO, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A.andP;  1991 JAN 15 (NB) -- A &quot;black box&quot; that lets Macintosh computerscontrol many consumer video products has been announced by Sony.andP;  The VBOXcontroller will give users complete remote control over most Sony products.andM;The VBOX (which is in fact white and is about the size of a paperback book)uses Sony's proprietary LANC remote control commands and its ViSCA machinecontrol protocols.andP;  To date, only Sony video devices include a LANC port --specifically, all 8mm products and other products sold after the introductionof 8mm.andP;  While Sony plans to eventually publish the specifications to ViSCA,officials told Newsbytes there are no plans to build hardware that will bringthe LANC and ViSCA protocols to equipment that doesn't have them alreadybuilt in.andM;Among the Sony products that include LANC capabilites are 8mm camcorders,Video 8 tape decks, VHS and Beta VCR recorders, and laserdisc players.andM;When Apple finishes writing drivers for the VBOX, Sony officials said, userswill be able to control video equipment in much the same way they controlprinters and disk drives -- in effect, printing to and retrieving data fromvideo.andM;One of the breakthroughs incorporated in the VBOX is the price.andP;  Whenavailable early in the spring, it will have a retail price of $250, Sonyofficials said.andP;  One VBOX is needed for each device to be controlled,  but upto seven of them can be daisy-chained together.andM;Sony said Farallon and Macromind intend to incorporate ViSCA technology intotheir products in 1991.andP;  Other software publishers are also known to beinterested.andM;(Daniel J. Rosenbaum/19910113/Press Contact: Mark Rozeen, TechnologySolutions, 212 505 9900)</TEXT></DOC>